  * Add CHECK_MINIMAL_VERSION support, so that the release manager can
    combine speedy uploads and peace of mind.

 -- Cyril Brulebois <kibi@debian.org>  Fri, 26 May 2023 09:08:23 +0200

debian-installer (20230515) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Bump Linux kernel ABI to 6.1.0-9.
  * Switch source format from 1.0 to 3.0 (native).
  * Update translation-status for the release.
  * Add temporary workaround for broken graphics when using the “bochs”
    graphics driver (default in QEMU, where it is known as “std”) or the
    “cirrus” one, under UEFI/Secure Boot (See: #1036019):
     - The previous upload seems to trigger a color depth mismatch between
       GRUB which defaults to 24 bpp in its bochs and cirrus video
       modules, and Linux (efifb, built-in) that reports 32 bpp.
     - This affects both the text installer and the graphical installer.
     - To avoid running into those issues, and until a better solution is
       determined, ship extra DRM modules for those graphics drivers:
       bochs.ko, cirrus.ko, plus their dependencies.
     - Limit the workaround to amd64, arm64, and i386 (where UEFI/Secure
       Boot are relevant), when drm.ko is detected in the build tree,
       copying files from the relevant linux-image package.
     - Add linux-image-6.1.0-9-amd64-{amd64,arm64,686,686-pae} to
       Build-Depends accordingly.
  * Many thanks to Ben Hutchings for the kernel-side insights!

 -- Cyril Brulebois <kibi@debian.org>  Mon, 15 May 2023 03:33:27 +0000

